wfBootpRelayIntfTable.name: wfBootpRelayIntfTable
wfBootpRelayIntfTable.description: This table contains per-interface configuration information for BOOTP relay agent operation

wfBootpRelayIntfEntry.name: wfBootpRelayIntfEntry
wfBootpRelayIntfEntry.description: a BOOTP relay agent interface description

wfBootpRelayIntfDelete.name: wfBootpRelayIntfDelete
wfBootpRelayIntfDelete.description: Create/Delete: if set to delete, the BOOTP relay agent is removed from this network interface

wfBootpRelayIntfDisable.name: wfBootpRelayIntfDisable
wfBootpRelayIntfDisable.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the BOOTP relay agent is enabled or disabled on this network interface

wfBootpRelayIntfState.name: wfBootpRelayIntfState
wfBootpRelayIntfState.description: the state if the BOOTP relay agent on this interface

wfBootpRelayIntfHops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfHops
wfBootpRelayIntfHops.description: maximum hop count. BOOTREQUESTs with a larger hops field will be dropped

wfBootpRelayIntfSeconds.name: wfBootpRelayIntfSeconds
wfBootpRelayIntfSeconds.description: minimum seconds. BOOTREQUESTs with a smaller seconds field will be dropped

wfBootpRelayIntfOpDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfOpDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfOpDrops.description: the total number of BOOTP packets received on this interface that were dropped because of an invalid operation field

wfBootpRelayIntfRequests.name: wfBootpRelayIntfRequests
wfBootpRelayIntfRequests.description: the total number of BOOTREQUEST packets received on this interface

wfBootpRelayIntfTranReqs.name: wfBootpRelayIntfTranReqs
wfBootpRelayIntfTranReqs.description: the total number of forwarded BOOTREQUEST packets received on this interface that contained a non-zero value in the gateway IP address field. This interface did not act as a relay agent for these packets

wfBootpRelayIntfHopsDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfHopsDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfHopsDrops.description: the total number of forwarded BOOTREQUEST packets received on this interface that were dropped due to a hops field that was too large

wfBootpRelayIntfBcastDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfBcastDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfBcastDrops.description: the total number of forwarded BOOTREQUEST packets received on this interface that were dropped due to a destination IP address that was not 255.255.255.255

wfBootpRelayIntfSecDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfSecDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfSecDrops.description: the total number of forwarded BOOTREQUEST packets received on this interface that were dropped due to a seconds field that was too small

wfBootpRelayIntfReplies.name: wfBootpRelayIntfReplies
wfBootpRelayIntfReplies.description: the total number of BOOTPREPLY packets received that were addressed to this interface

wfBootpRelayIntfGiaddrDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfGiaddrDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfGiaddrDrops.description: the total number of BOOTPREPLY packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because the giaddr field was not the same as the interface's address

wfBootpRelayIntfResrcDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfResrcDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfResrcDrops.description: the total number of BOOTPREPLY packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because sufficient resources were not available

wfBootpRelayIntfPassThroughMode.name: wfBootpRelayIntfPassThroughMode
wfBootpRelayIntfPassThroughMode.description: The ACCEPTANCE mode for this interface: Bootp Requests only, both Bootp Requests and Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages, or Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages only.

wfBootpRelayIntfUdpSktDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfUdpSktDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfUdpSktDrops.description: The total number of BOOTP packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because the UDP socket field is not BOOTPS (67).

wfBootpRelayIntfTooShortDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfTooShortDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfTooShortDrops.description: The total number of BOOTP packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because the UDP length field is too short.

wfBootpRelayIntfFltrDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfFltrDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfFltrDrops.description: The total number of BOOTPREQUEST packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because this type of packet is filtered off by the Pass Through Mode

wfBootpRelayIntfPri.name: wfBootpRelayIntfPri
wfBootpRelayIntfPri.description: Indicates priority of the interface on a multinetted interface

wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvrDsbl.name: wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvrDsbl
wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvrDsbl.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the DHCP Server is enabled or disabled on this network interface.

wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvDnDrps.name: wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvDnDrps
wfBootpRelayIntfDhcpSvDnDrps.description: The total number of BOOTPREQUEST packets received that were addressed to this interface and dropped because this packet was a DHCP packet that should have been handled by the DHCP Server subsystem, but the subsystem was down.

wfBootpRelayIntfArpCache.name: wfBootpRelayIntfArpCache
wfBootpRelayIntfArpCache.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the BOOTP relay agent will add/update an ARP entry based on the information contained in a BOOTP reply message (not applicable for DHCP)

wfBootpRelayIntfBufLimit.name: wfBootpRelayIntfBufLimit
wfBootpRelayIntfBufLimit.description: The total unprocessed number of BOOTP/DHCP request/reply packets allowed in this interface. See CR147895-1 for detail

wfBootpRelayIntfBufDrops.name: wfBootpRelayIntfBufDrops
wfBootpRelayIntfBufDrops.description: The total number of BOOTP request/reply packets dropped due to the wfBootpRelayIntfBufLimit is arrived.

wfBootpRelayFwdTable.name: wfBootpRelayFwdTable
wfBootpRelayFwdTable.description: for a BOOTP relay agent on a given interface, this table contains the list of interfaces through which that agent will forward BOOTREQUEST packets

wfBootpRelayFwdDelete.name: wfBootpRelayFwdDelete
wfBootpRelayFwdDelete.description: Create/Delete: if set to delete, the forwarding entry is removed from the table

wfBootpRelayFwdDisable.name: wfBootpRelayFwdDisable
wfBootpRelayFwdDisable.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the the forwarding entry is active or not

wfBootpRelayFwdPassThroughMode.name: wfBootpRelayFwdPassThroughMode
wfBootpRelayFwdPassThroughMode.description: The PROPAGATION mode for this interface: Bootp Requests only, both Bootp Requests and Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages, or Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages only.

wfBootpRelayFwdOutReqPkts.name: wfBootpRelayFwdOutReqPkts
wfBootpRelayFwdOutReqPkts.description: The total number of BOOTPREQUEST packets relayed out of this forwarding entry.

wfBootpClientIntfTable.name: wfBootpClientIntfTable
wfBootpClientIntfTable.description: for a BOOTP relay agent on a given interface, this table contains the list of DLCI-IP address assignments.

wfBootpClientIntfDelete.name: wfBootpClientIntfDelete
wfBootpClientIntfDelete.description: Flag to indicate BOOTP client interface instance deletion

wfBootpClientIntfDlci.name: wfBootpClientIntfDlci
wfBootpClientIntfDlci.description: The DLCI for the virtual circuit used by this BOOTP client

wfBootpClientIntfAddress.name: wfBootpClientIntfAddress
wfBootpClientIntfAddress.description: The IP address for the interface used by this BOOTP client

wfBootpRelayPrefServTable.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServTable
wfBootpRelayPrefServTable.description: This table contains Preferred Server configuration information for configured Bootp Relay Agents.

wfBootpRelayPrefServEntry.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServEntry
wfBootpRelayPrefServEntry.description: a BOOTP relay Preferred Server description

wfBootpRelayPrefServDelete.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServDelete
wfBootpRelayPrefServDelete.description: Create/Delete: if set to delete, the static entry is removed from the table

wfBootpRelayPrefServDisable.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServDisable
wfBootpRelayPrefServDisable.description: Enable/Disable: controls whether the static entry is included in the list of preferred servers for this interface or not.

wfBootpRelayPrefServTargetAddress.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServTargetAddress
wfBootpRelayPrefServTargetAddress.description: Target Server(s) address, either unicast or multicast

wfBootpRelayPrefServRequestMode.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServRequestMode
wfBootpRelayPrefServRequestMode.description: The PROPAGATION mode for this preferred server: Bootp Requests only, both Bootp Requests and Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages, or Bootp Requests containing DHCP messages only.

wfBootpRelayPrefServOutReqPkts.name: wfBootpRelayPrefServOutReqPkts
wfBootpRelayPrefServOutReqPkts.description: The total number of BOOTPREQUEST packets relayed to this preferred server.
